<subSubSection id="3872FB64A840380C880F30E3C67EF308" pageId="null" pageNumber="258" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="3D1467D2107BEF1C9F97CF9F107B617B" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Nabelkraut</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="E4C9E515FD84FBE0C60BB09D285E642B" pageId="null" pageNumber="258" type="description">
<paragraph id="F792DD6158385DA6D6C253C05F866AD2" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">
Ausdauernd, oberirdische Teile jedoch im Herbst absterbend. 
<emphasis id="63D15E2734ABB03FAC89C347DAEED2D9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Wurzeln knollig verdickt.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="A9983E612BACE9F59CA1CBD4EF746833" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
fleischig, flach, 
<emphasis id="D63DF7C6DFB4D9647F5FBCD1DD314824" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">
<normalizedToken id="54BB2B577AE21766EBB98DA79945AB49" originalValue="schildförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">schildfoermig</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="02E4B3DF3117B584EA40929C26A9B483" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
eine Traube oder Rispe. 
<normalizedToken id="4E851B407658CDA3AB69C242B7E4C27F" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Blueten</normalizedToken>
5 
<normalizedToken id="98E141C3A7003BD8BC08EAD674C1EA03" originalValue="zählig" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">zaehlig</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="C23808BB546B3796CA761CF6485B2F3E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">
<normalizedToken id="8A36DC23462735B04DBEFF7E8D14CCC0" originalValue="Kronblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Kronblaetter</normalizedToken>
oft fast in der ganzen 
<normalizedToken id="6583091F84D278D547C2B692C56256E0" originalValue="Länge" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Laenge</normalizedToken>
verwachsen;
</emphasis>
Krone zylindrisch oder 
<normalizedToken id="83D4E9767134FA83EA468606D17AD2A3" originalValue="glockenförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">glockenfoermig</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="05290E73FF33E29A1E3C5DBC3B3BE778" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
10, selten 5. 
<normalizedToken id="C824BFC4A9BD9808CBCD0CA242F62B60" originalValue="Fruchtblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">Fruchtblaetter</normalizedToken>
5, frei.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CEA1554699C4913C48FFED6B50E6294B" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="F0FC2CD0C7D66F5383E17E30507329BF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">
<taxonomicName id="7BA73F70950A9B2F54AD7A8843A6F61E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Umbilicus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="null" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Umbilicus</taxonomicName>
ist im ganzen Mediterrangebiet verbreitet, in Afrika 
<normalizedToken id="5E08A3AD75358FF1E344BDD20E52C71D" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Abessinien, 
<normalizedToken id="C4BD9CB7C9A53A8032F569B411DF4F3B" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Persien. Sie 
<normalizedToken id="54AF30AEF8E65A11B6718B1CB3CF5A43" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="258">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 10 Arten.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
